snippet.textDisplay: If I understand what you're saying correctly, you're saying your soil's pH is 7.3 or 7.9, both of which are considered basic. Anything 6.9 and below would be considered acidic soil. Lots of grasses actually prefer a more acidic soil for optimum growing conditions. If your pH is high, fixing the issue may be as simple as adding sulfur to the soil to lower the pH. The amount to add for pH adjustment is dependent on soil type, and it's not an over night fix, but it shouldn't be very expensive.
